Alright now that I don't work here anymore the whole truth about what goes on behind the scenes here shall shine!  Lisa Conti, the freakishly ugly rhino-looking valium head who runs the cash register up front first of all thinks she's sixteen-years-old and loves to gossip about other employees and customers. Plus she is rude to the customers. She has dodged many bullets with HR and is a world class bully. She would corner me and threaten me with my job if I forgot to do even the most minuscule thing such as cleaning a toilet bowl knob.  SECONDLY you never get complimented or appreciated for your hard work at this job. Nothing goes appreciated. You only get yelled at more. Nothing is ever good enough and management is miserable. They have these cute and rather adolescent “team meetings” which always mess up the morning setup because it’s a complete waste of time and it occurs fifteen minutes for opening. Fake laughter. Fake cheers. Fake excitement.  I did my God damn job for the customers.  That very misery that the management carries- they love to rub off on the employees. Whatever stress the manager may be going through is completely brushed on to the employees they dislike the most. Bullying and favoritism is a H-U-G-E issue here.  The greatest employees are never treated with gratitude and/or promoted. A great worker who had been there 2 years would be ignored and the managerial position would go to that younger guy who just got off parole a week ago. Plus he only has that energy because he would do mad blow in the bathroom every day.  The employees (and I speak on behalf of the whole team there) are slaved, yelled at, treated like animals and are paid a whopping $13 for their hard work.  HR is never there (to answer the phone) for you and they always take management's side so they are useless.  I don’t even care about how unprofessional this seems, it had to be said.

I had picked the spicy tofu, which had zero flavor, and I'd also picked the spicy garlic sauce (couldn't tell you what that even was because I didn't detect any flavor from that). I'd also asked for the sauce on the side, which didn't happen, and the portion was tiny tiny for the $9+ dollars. I'd also ordered for my boyfriend, and he had picked chicken and just the regular garlic sauce. The chicken was just very boring, mushy boiled chicken, and there's just ZERO flavor. The vegetables that we both picked seemed fresh, which is about the only positive thing I can say about this. Even the noodles were bland.
